## Polymorphism
 - Employee[] arr = new Employee[3];
 - Without polymorphism -> only same type can be stored

 - arr[0] = new Employee("홍길동", 2000);
   arr[1] = new Manager("유관순", 4000, "관리");
   arr[2] = new Engineer("이순신", 4300, "자바");
 - With polymorphism -> child types can also be stored


 - Object[] obj = new Object[3];
   obj[0] = new Employee();
	 obj[1] = "문자열";
	 obj[2] = 123;
 - Object array -> can store all data types in java


 ## Package & Import
  - Purpose : Class file management (similar to folders)
  - Convention : Domain in reverse order com.google
  - Default package : Auto-assigned when no package is specified
  - Same Package : No import needed
  - Different package : Import required
  - Java.lang : No import needed
  - Different package : Same class name can be used

## Interface

 - // Multiple implementation possible!
 - public class A extends B implements interface1, interface2    {
     public void a() { }  // Must be overridden!
   }

 - // Multiple inheritance between interfaces possible!
 - public interface C extends interface 1, interface 2 { }
